{{refimprove|date=June 2017}}
'''The Society of Catholic Social Scientists''' is a [[non-profit organization]] founded in 1992 by Dr. Stephen M. Krason, Esq., of the [[Franciscan University]] of [[Steubenville, Ohio]] at the [[Pittsburgh Hilton]] Hotel and recognized as a non-profit by the [[United States Internal Revenue Service]] in 1999.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guidestar.org/profile/34-1825616|title=SOCIETY OF CATHOLIC SOCIAL SCIENTIST INC - GuideStar Profile|website=www.guidestar.org|language=en|access-date=2017-06-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last= Varacalli |first=Joseph A.|date= 1996 |title=Society Of Catholic Social Scientists: Catholic Social Science And The Reconstruction Of The Social Order, The|url=https://www.catholicculture.org/culture/library/view.cfm?recnum=3903 |magazine=Faith & Reason|location= Front Royal, VA |publisher= Christendom Press |pages=3-14 |access-date= 19 August 2017 }}</ref>. The SCSS offers a [[M.Th]]. in Catholic Social Thought at Steubenville, Ohio<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gtfeducation.org/about-the-gtf/society-of-catholic-social-scientists.cfm |title=Society of Catholic Social Scientists |last= |first= |date= 2017 |website= Graduate Theological Foundation |publisher= |access-date=19 August 2017 |quote=}}</ref>, as well as holding an annual meeting and conference<ref>{{cite web |url=https://cardinalnewmansociety.org/20th-anniversary-society-of-catholic-social-scientists-conference-announced/ |title=20th Anniversary Society of Catholic Social Scientists Conference Announced|last=Wilson |first=Adam |date=10 August 2012 |website=The Cardinal Newman Society |publisher= |access-date= 19 August 2017 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.franciscan.edu/Events/Talks-Conferences-Symposia/Society-of-Catholic-Social-Scientists--25th-Annual-Conference/ |title=Catholic Social Scientists to Meet October 27-28 at Franciscan University |last= |first= |date=2017 |website=Franciscan University of Steubenville |publisher= |access-date= 19 August 2017 |quote=}}</ref> and an [[academic journal]], ''The Catholic Social Science Review''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/25th-annual-society-of-catholic-social-scientists-national-meeting-and-conference-tickets-36449651890 |title= 25th Annual Society of Catholic Social Scientists National Meeting and Conference |last= |first= |date=2017 |website=Eventbrite |publisher= |access-date= 19 August 2017 |quote=}}</ref>
The organization's mission is to "bring rigorous, credible scholarship to political, social and economic questions" through a collegiality of Catholic scholars, professors, researchers, practitioners, and writers who "approach their work in both a scholarly and evangelical spirit."<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.catholicsocialscientists.org/Content/Organization|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090201234009/http://www.catholicsocialscientists.org/Content/Organization/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2009-02-01|title=index.asp|website=www.catholicsocialscientists.org|access-date=2017-06-27}}</ref> The organization publishes the Catholic Social Science Review - an interdisciplinary, peer-reviewed journal of original articles and reviews in the social sciences and the humanities.
They are expected to strictly observe the highest scholarly and professional requirements of their disciplines as they examine their data in light of Church teaching and the Natural Law. In this way, the Society seeks to obtain objective knowledge about the social order, provide solutions to vexing social problems, and further the cause of Christ.
